# Home Lab Network Project

## Overview
Built a virtual network using Windows and Ubuntu VMs in VirtualBox.

## Configuration
- Internal Network: 192.168.10.0/24
- Windows IP: 192.168.10.10
- Ubuntu IP: 192.168.10.20
- NAT used for internet access

## What I Did
- Installed and configured Ubuntu in a VM
- Set up dual network adapters (Internal + NAT)
- Assigned static IP addresses
- Enabled firewall rules for ICMP
- Troubleshot connectivity issues

## Verification
- Successful ping between Windows and Ubuntu systems

## Skills Demonstrated
- Networking fundamentals (TCP/IP)
- Linux system configuration
- Windows network configuration
- Troubleshooting connectivity issues
